=MOON1-1 Nature's Wrath===
{{Main|Nature's Wrath}}
{{Quote|''Faith in Chauntea runs strong amongst the Ffolk, and the village of Warlsbry is no exception. The village has fallen from favor and now the beasts of field and sea bring their wrath against the village. You must return the village to her good graces or it will not survive the coming winter. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in The Moonshae Isles for characters levels 1&ndash;4.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Michael Mockus]]
* '''Released:''' September 2008
* '''Levels:''' 1{{st}} &ndash; 4{{th}}

===MOON1-2 The Sea Drake===
{{Main|The Sea Drake}}
{{Quote|''Valiant seafarers travel between the Moonshae Isles, bringing supplies and information to the many people. You have been hired as guard aboard the ''Sea Drake''. The weather is rainy and the fog is thick. It's a perfect time to sail the seas of the Moonshaes. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in The Moonshae Isles for characters levels 4&ndash;7.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jean-Philipe Chapleau]]
* '''Released:''' October 2008
* '''Levels:''' 4{{th}} &ndash; 7{{th}}

===MOON1-3 Black Gold===
{{Main|Black Gold}}
{{Quote|''Dirty Barnison got his treasure, a mysterious, metallic stone. A visiting noble from a faraway land now asks you to help him find some more of it, and he is willing to pay for your efforts. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in The Moonshae Isles for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Leonard Logan]]
* '''Released:''' February 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

===MOON1-4 Black Blood===
{{Main|Black Blood}}
{{Quote|''The Black Blood tribe holds sway over much of the island of Moray. An ambitious young man wants to break their power and make the island safe again. However, he cannot do it alone. Part 2 of "The Fisherman" Major Quest. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in the Moonshae Isles for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jean-Philipe Chapleau]]
* '''Released:''' April 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

===MOON1-5 Lost Love===
{{Main|Lost Love}}
{{Quote|''Moonshadow, an old eladrin adventurer, has been missing for years. Though long enough to be forgotten by man, an eladrin's life is much longer than most. An old love seeks to learn his fate. This adventure begins or continues the "Fey Gates of the Sea of Swords" major quest that started in BALD1-5 ''Lost Refuge''. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in The Moonshae Isles for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Mick Hand]]
* '''Released:''' September 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

===MOON1-6 Black Heart===
{{Main|Black Heart}}
{{Quote|''As if the lycanthropes of Moray, the giants of Oman and the beasts of Norland were not enough, something evil and dangerous lurks in the dark corners of what used to be the most civilized island of the Moonshae. Occupied Snowdown has need for heroes, and soon. Something about vampires roaming the streets of Westphal&hellip; Choose your friends well and your enemies better. This is the conclusion of "The Fisherman" major quest. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in The Moonshae Isles for characters levels 11&ndash;14.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Jean-Philipe Chapleau]]
* '''Released:''' November 2009
* '''Levels:''' 11{{th}} &ndash; 14{{th}}

===MOON1-7 Treasure Hunt===
{{Main|Treasure Hunt (Living Forgotten Realms)}}
{{Quote|''An old bard's tale, a sunken ship, and a foreign captain: Secrets lost for decades may come to light if you embark on this treasure hunt. You may find riches or be the main course on some beast's table. Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in the Moonshae Isles for characters levels 7&ndash;10.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Timmy Creese]]
* '''Released:''' December 2009
* '''Levels:''' 7{{th}} &ndash; 10{{th}}

===MOON2-1 Darkness Falls over Moray===
{{Main|Darkness Falls over Moray}}
{{Quote|''Only a sliver of light separates those who profit and those who perish on the island of Moray. When that light is extinguished, it is difficult for even the greatest heroes to find their way. A Living Forgotten Realms adventure set in The Moonshae Isles for characters levels 4&ndash;7.''}}
* '''Designer(s):''' [[Louis Giersch]]
* '''Released:''' February 2010
* '''Levels:''' 4{{th}} &ndash; 7{{th}}

